The paper deals with the problem of preserving privacy while publishing spatiotemporal trajectory datasets, which is a common concern in the field of database systems (cs.DB) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves the use of machine learning techniques such as clustering and alignment, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the analysis of the performance of the proposed approach, which can be considered as an evaluation of a computational method (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of anonymization of sensitive data, which is a topic of interest in the field of social and information networks (cs.SI).
